>[Question]
>How would I go about finding the diagonal measurement of a rectangle?
>
>[Difficulty]
>I don't know what formula to use.
>
>[Thoughts]
>

Thanks for writing to Ask Dr. Math, Mike!

If the rectangle's sides are A and B, and the diagonal length is C,
then

   C = sqrt(A^2+B^2),

by the Pythagorean Theorem.

Feel free to reply if I can help further with this question.


